; Cyclic-goal detection demo.
; A rule that tries to prove A from A creates an immediate self-loop.
; The runtime detects this and drops the looping goal before it spawns
; infinite work.

; Seed
; No fact for A — the only available path is the self-loop.

; Rules
(ruleN (A $x) 1.0 1.0 (pcons (A $x) pnil))
(, (Goal (A x)))
(goal-path (A x) pnil)
(fact (D x) (1.0 1.0))
